Class Population

java.lang.Object
Population
public class Population
extends java.lang.Object
This class represents the data structure which holds a Population representation.

      replaceFraction - A double which indicates the fraction of worst elements to be replaced with the best elements.

    • offspring

      public void offspring​(Population parents, java.util.Random ran, double crossOverProbability)
      Add all the individuals obtained from the crossover, until the current population is full.
      Parameters:
      parents - The population which will be used to perform crossover.
      ran - An instance of a Random number generator, which is used to apply crossover.
      crossOverProbability - The probability for which crossover occurs.

    • mutatePopulation

      public void mutatePopulation​(java.util.Random ran, double mutationProbability)
      Mutate each individual of the given population, with a given probability. In this case, two bit swap mutation is used. After applying the mutation operator in the population, the population fitness is updated.
      Parameters:
      ran - An instance of a Random Number generator, which is used to apply mutation.
      mutationProbability - The probability for which mutation will occur.
